Pipe output from duplicate-key-checker into another tool to graph structures 
   (check out dot for graphing)
mysqldiff: http://www.adamspiers.org/computing/mysqldiff/
query sniper:
   * http://www.stillhq.com/mysql/000008.html
mysql-binlog-pipeliner: read ahead in the binlog (SHOW BINLOG EVENTS) and rewrite queries and pre-warm the cache.
http://www.mysqlperformanceblog.com/2007/05/22/wishes-for-mysqldump/
* mysql-slave-delay
* read binlogs from many servers and apply them to one.

* Allow daemonization:

use POSIX 'setsid';

sub daemonize {
   chdir '/' or die "Can't chdir to /: $!";
   open STDIN, '/dev/null' or die "Can't read /dev/null: $!";
   open STDOUT, '>/dev/null' or die "Can't write to /dev/null: $!";
   defined( my $pid = fork ) or die "Can't fork: $!";
   exit if $pid;
   setsid or die "Can't start a new session: $!";
   open STDERR, '>&STDOUT' or die "Can't dup stdout: $!";
}
